<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-098-270  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 098 270.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Feb 27 1989 v23 n8 p103(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Layoffs-plus as Unisys cuts costs.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Margolis, Nell.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Unisys Corp quietly fields an inventory-reduction plan, avoluntary retirement plan and a major workforce reduction in anongoing effort to contain costs during a difficult producttransition that yielded poor 4th-qtr earnings.andP;  The $10 billionfirm eliminates some 1,700 US-based employee positions as part ofa plan to trim the workforce by three percent by the end of 1989;the reductions hit 190 personnel at headquarters in Blue Bell, PA,in marketing, administration and engineering.andP;  Certain engineeringand development operations in Blue Bell are to be consolidatedwith a similar, larger operation at a Roseville, MN, plant; 100engineering positions in Blue Bell are being done away withimmediately, with another 400 to go by Jul 1989.andP;  An assemblyplant in Mexico will also be closed, canceling 400 jobs.andP;  Thevoluntary retirement and voluntary layoff programs covers 900 to1,000 US employees.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Unisys Corp. (layoffs).andO;Ticker:    UIS.andO;Topic:     Computer industryLayoffCost Reduction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>